      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The \"tough, street-smart Latino guy\" is usually depicted as a macho, wisecracking, fast-talking, beer-guzzling, sports-loving, rugged individualist who always has a clever quip at the ready. He's often portrayed with a thick accent, using over-the-top slang and idioms that are supposed to be \"authentically\" Latino, but really just come across as caricatured and cringeworthy. And don't even get me started on the \"nerdy Indian character\" - they're usually depicted as being super awkward, with a lisp, and speaking in a stilted, overly formal tone, often using words like \"gadzooks\" and \"whilst\". They're also often shown to be obsessed with science, technology, engineering, and math (STEM) subjects, and are frequently the butt of jokes about being \"good with numbers\" or \"a genius\". These stereotypes are so ridiculous that they're ripe for parody.",
